content:
@Pidgeon: I'm inclined to be skeptical of meta reads in general unless they are really strong, and a read based on a single game that nobody here was in doesn't seem very strong to me, especially when he's doing so much other scummy stuff.  There are lots of reasons people might be playing differently from one game to another that aren't related to alignment.<br>
<br>
@Masnev: Could you summarize the thrust of your Paschendale case in 1-2 sentences?  Normally I'd just go look at the post where you voted him but you've been voting him since RVS so I'm just interested to know where your argument is now.

@image: If triton's claim is fake, what do you think was his motive for faking it?  Did he intend to provoke this reaction from the town?<br>
<br>
@Pidgeon: Surprised at your change of opinion on triton.  I think your idea of triton over-emphasizing his noob status requires a calculatedness that I just don't see in triton's play.<br>
<br>
@Masnev: I felt like putting some kind of pressure on image was the only way I was going to be able to get any kind of read on him because of his super cautious posting style.  I just wasn't getting anything out of his first posts.<br>
<br>
In response to your numbered questions:<br>
1. The nervous/resigned tone to the series of posts where he claims feels very genuine to me.  As a "logical" scum maneuver, it makes no sense, and I said above, if it is faked, it requires a level of calculation that I just don't see anywhere else in his play (e.g. it seems like he genuinely feels that a pbpa of AngryPidgeon is helpful right now).<br>
2. Maybe I should have made my point clearer.  What I found shady wasn't that image was attacking triton in general, it's that he was attacking the claim post specifically.  I just don't know how you can read that post and not get townvibes from it.<br>
3. Well, yes, that's been clear from the beginning.  His jump on you (or one of your heads, I don't remember) early looked like something newbie scum would try.

@Masnev: Tried to get a scum read on you for a while, but I couldn't get a good one that wasn't some stretch. It's one of the few reasons I think you're town.<br>
<br>
@Gutter:  <img class="smilies" src="./images/smilies/icon_confused.gif" width="15" height="15" alt=":?" title="Confused"> I don't want you to just sheep AP. If you do, are you open to the possibility that both AP is wrong about me, and that we're both town? Or do you believe AP should be lynched if I flip VT?

@Masnev: I tend to trust Miller claims early on.  Also mainly a gut read.  I just didn't see him being scum.  I really really don't get his posts about UCT though and they bother me.<br>
<br>
@Shamrock: You know you could ISO me and look for the quote walls that have "Vector" in them.  Pretty much I feel a lot of his push on TP42 is easy/fake and a lot of his posts are just directing noise around and lacking of hard stances on anything.

Would like to see an answer to why Hoopla is posting all of this Guttersnipe analysis if it doesn't necessarily give her a read on him. Hoopla, who should we be lynching today?<br>
<br>
@Snifit: <blockquote><div><cite>snifit wrote:</cite>Does anyone think AngryPidgeon is town?</div></blockquote><br>
<br>
Yes, as a matter of fact, I do. Don't you? Why (other than that Shamrock thing you mentioned)?<br>
<br>
@Shamrock: What do you think of the accusations that AP brought up against you?<br>
<br>
@Guttersnipe: Do you still think TP42 is scum? What do you think of his doc claim?

@Tech:<br>
<br>
If TP42 dies today, I don't think Hoopla is an auto lynch.  Snifit dodged that ? when I asked him and FLP said he wouldn't auto lynch Hoopla.  And even if we do get scum Hoopla Tomorrow, it wont tell us much about her team.  Her death would have been fairly inevitable at that point.  And there is still the slight chance of them both being town at which point we've pretty much auto lost.  So, I don't think a TP42 townflip puts us in a good position at MyLo.  Especially since if I am correct, then you will die tonight without vigging anyone.  If we lynch outside of TP42/Hoopla though that puts the pressure back on the scum team to analyze the best play and try not to out-WIFOM themselves.  It also makes the potential cop a little safer since we will have a doc around (assuming TP42 town).

@ChaosOmega<br>
Are you willing to hammer TP? You thought he was scummy enough to run him up yesterday. Has your read changed? Or are you just not willing to lynch scum that fakeclaims a PR? Or the excluded middle?<br>
<br>
@Tech<br>
Fate will often hammer people who get to L-1 and save the town the agony of the hemming and hawing that often goes on before a lynch.<br>
I dislike his playstyle, but he's a damn good scum hunter.
